#Text=Get Away With Going to a Site You Are n't Supposed To
#Text=Are you not allowed to go on a website , say , YouTube or Myspace ?
#Text=Well , for whatever reason it may be , you want to go on that site .
#Text=Maybe a friend told you of a cool video on YouTube , or maybe your friend has a page on Myspace they want you to see .
#Text=Either way , its important you make sure you do n't get caught doing this .
#Text=Someone could see you on the site , or they could tell you were there from the browser 's history .
#Text=Please read on to find out how to cover your tracks when you have to go on a site you are n't allowed to visit .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Open up your browser and go to the history .
#Text=Make sure there is some history left behind you before you go to the site .
#Text=If there is n't much , go to some sites , like yahoo and just click on links to fill up the history .
#Text=Once you have some history built , go to the site you are n't allowed to .
#Text=The point of filling up history before is because the site you went to will get " blurred in " and " lost " with the other pages .
#Text=You should also get a few other windows opened up .
#Text=This way , if someone comes by , you can just change windows .
#Text=Look at whatever you need to look at .
#Text=Be sure you do n't take long though .
#Text=Close the window .
#Text=You should do this just to be sure you do n't get caught .
#Text=This is also where having multiple windows open helps , as you can now fill up more history .
#Text=Delete whatever history you had on that site .
#Text=You can now begin filling up history again .
#Text=Go on another site your parents allow you to .
#Text=Once you are there , go back and forth and click on as many links as you can .
#Text=Do this quickly however so it looks like you were only there for the whole time .
#Text=Tips

#Text=Try getting Firefox then go to Tools > Options ... > Privacy and check the box " Always clear private data when I close Firefox " then go to settings and check/uncheck whatever you want to be erased or kept .
#Text=Do n't use AOL 9.0
#Text=you ca n't delete the web history .
#Text=Be careful and make up some excuses for what you are doing .
#Text=Also delete the temporary internet files and cookies .
#Text=If there is a web filter on your computer , use a proxy web surfer to surf the sites , and then delete the history afterwards .
#Text=Try downloading an internet explorer that has a porn mode were you can delete history easily
#Text=Search the website 's name on Google instead of entering it into the address bar .
#Text=If you do , the bad website 's name will be in the address bar and your parent[s ] will notice .
#Text=Be sure to delete the Google search history too .
#Text=If you would like to bookmark a website add it to you favorites with an innocent looking name .
#Text=For example " This History of the Airplane Telephone " .
#Text=Warnings
#Text=You could get grounded if you do this .
#Text=Please do this at your own risk .
#Text=Things
#Text=You 'll Need
#Text=Internet browser
#Text=Internet history
#Text=A few windows
#Text=open
#Text=Proxy
#Text=web surfer ( such as Proxify.com or vtunnel.com )
